FBIS4-36717 "drnes113_p_94004" FBIS-NES-94-113 Daily Report 12 Jun 1994 SOUTH ASIA Afghanistan Twelve Killed, 100 Wounded in Shindand Fighting Twelve Killed, 100 Wounded in Shindand Fighting LD1206202494 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network in Persian 1930 GMT 12 Jun 94 LD1206202494 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network Persian BFN [Text] Intense clashes between President Borhanoddin Rabbani's forces and the opposition forces continued in the Shindand region of Herat Province for the second consecutive day. According to a report released by the coalition opposed to Rabbani's presidency, 12 people were killed and 100 others were wounded. The coalition sources added that fighting continues in Qurmash region as well as in Badgheys Province, and the opposition forces have captured some positions of the government troops in this region.
